Subject: Re: [T2] thermostat in '71 1600 air cleaner



On Mon, 5 Nov 2001, Jack Dinan wrote:

> My questions:
> 1. Can anyone explain the mechanism inside the thermostat? It must be more
> than a bimetallic strip.  The force on the plunger must be quite strong to
> counteract that long spring.

It's called a "wax pellet" thermostat.  Expanding wax pushes a plunger in
and out to open and close the flap.

> 2. Does anyone happen to have a thermostat + plunger to sell me?

No, but I live quite happily with my inoperative thermostat.  I wired the
flap in the open position and simply remove and reinstall the hot air tube
at either end of the hot months.

George Lyle

